HEADWORD: Malformation
<hw>Mal`for*ma"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Mal-</ets> + <ets>formation</ets>.]</ety> <def>Ill formation;
irregular or anomalous formation; abnormal or wrong conformation or
structure; -- often used of body parts such as limbs which do not
develop properly during fetal maturation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Malgracious</ent>⟦br⟧
